      Compared to monoliths like Gatsby or Hugo, it is easy to see what Metalsmith does. Even fairly sophisticated plugins can be written by taking advantadge of node plugins, and there are a myriad of them.

      Metalsmith lay dormant for a while. It was initially created by  [Segment](https://segment.com/) in early 2014. But after a couple of years the project languished. 

      Recently, a new lead developer/maintainer Kevin Van Lierde AKA [webketje](https://github.com/webketje) has taken over and Metalsmith is now again under active development. [Read more about this history here](https://www.metalsmith.io/about/).

